caption: Nice Cafe for snacks n fun.

Nice place to try India fusion food.  Just they should increase the  serving size of the food . According to what they charge food is little. Definitely you have to order more than 2 to 3 items to get full.
There are super slow... I ordered 7.00 pm and almost 1hour 20mins they served👎🏻👎🏻
I really enjoyed the food and appreciated the outstanding hospitality by the staff. Only wish the wait wasn't long. I recommend making a reservation ahead of time.

All the food my friend and I ordered were really tasty. We loved the vibe of the place and the waitresses were really friendly.  Heads up they close from 4pm-5pm to get ready for the dinner patrons.  We ordered the fuska, saag paneer, chicken tikka mac and cheese, lemon rice and garlic butter naan. I think my only gripe was that we couldn’t try their masala chai. The waitress told us it was only available after 5pm. I’ll have to go back for dinner then haha! Oh and their lemon rice didn’t taste as lemony and seasoned as I thought it would be? As I compared it to the white rice it kind of tasted about the same. I’ve only tried lemon rice one other time and I remembered it being more seasoned and lemony. But it wasn’t a big deal just want to give a heads up to others who want to order it. Perhaps this is just how the restaurant does it. Other than that everything else was superb.  Definitely coming back!!!

Got sick after eating the chicken tikka kati roll, the roll itself was not cooked properly. It is obvious the food was under cooked and contaminated. Also, be aware of the servers just adding tip on their own. Check your receipt!!

I would say this is a decent place for anyone wanting to try modern south asian food.  The service was good along with how the food was presented. The music was extremely loud though. When the food arrived, the portions were pretty small, and definitely not enough to justify the price. I found both the white rice and lemon rice was kind of hard and tasted old.  There should be a few more spicy options for the people who can handle it, but overall if you have no spice tolerance, this would be an okay place to dine out.
Quality? 2.5 out of 5 Price? 2.00 out of 5 Recommend? You can vit for one time.
Bad food and service is not good
Something different

UPDATE: 03/26/2021  Food was good, however they tried to charge an 18% service fee for a group of 4 when on the menu it states its charged for groups of 5 or more people. After I mentioned it they took it off. Be careful and be aware they don’t attempt to do the same to you and your group. Read the receipt carefully or else they’ll try to pull a fast one on you. ————————————————————————  11/20/2020 Good food, not so good 18% service charge for a party of 5 or more.
Too loud music and really hard to convince them that it’s really disturbing
Tasty food, wonderful atmosphere, and economical prices! I highly recommend some of the appetizers includes the chicken tikkah samosas or the chicken pop entree.
Super food and their behavior is awesome

The food was stale and not authentic ‘desi’ cuisine. For those reading this desi = Indian, Bangladeshi, Sri Lankan and Pakistani. The flavors  from all these countries are similar. But unfortunately not here. The vibe is good, the concept is good but the food is off!
Great dining experience!
Good food. The lamb biryani, pani Puri, butter chicken, chicken tandoori were all good. Loud music though
Really love the atmosphere here. The food is great.  The staff are super friendly and the service is perfect. Also they have a riksha for photo ops.

Visited on a cold night, indoor seating and plexiglass dividers between seats. Felt comfortable dining, good atmosphere. There's a Rikshaw in the front for decoration, good vibes idk if you can go on and take a pic. Sajina was our server. We ordered Chicken Tikka Mac & Cheese app was really good, but the Chicken Tikka Samosa took it home for me, that was my favorite app. Overall good service and good food. Will return.
Shanzida this girl is the sweetest! She gave us the best service Ive seen compared to other places. The food was delicious!
Great place and love the decor
Honestly the service was amazing !!!!! Thanks to the beautiful shanzida  who gives the best service ever !!!! Love her !!!

My favorite places to go for good Indian street food! I cannot say enough good things about the Aloo Unda Kati Roll! Unbelievably delicious! I dream about it.Their Saag has a bit of a kick, which is unique and so good. Their Mango Lassi is also very good. Great place!

I was looking forward to trying Gully as I had heard good things, but was absolutely disappointed by the food. Food, in general, lacked flavor. How do you serve dahi poori without tamarind chutney? Aloo tikki was below average and again lacked sauces and flavor. The gobi manchurian likely saved the night for us. Also, give your customers a heads up that they will be served bottled water and will be charged extra! I don't mind paying, but can you imagine the number of water bottles they are going through a night and those ending up in a landfill? I am absolutely against the plastic bottles!! Anyway, back to the food..not worth all that hype in my opinion..
Thank you Shanzida for celebrating us being at your place and making our time special with your lively personality and amazing service. God bless you!  ❤💙
Decoration is really nice, foods are delicious!! Great staffs,  love the place

Wonderful dining experience! Very welcoming and extremely friendly staff. Love the atmosphere and the music! Everything we ordered was so delicious. They forgot my husbands entree but made it up with a free plate of fuska and brought his entree shortly. We will definitely go back, can’t wait to try more. Thanks guys
Idk what the hype is all about on social media! The food tasted bad and now I’m sick.
Overpriced & Overhyped. Not recommended.

Love this place! One of our favorite places in Queens. Chicken tikka Mac and cheese is definite go to as is the karahi and korma. Butter chicken was a bit sweet for us. Lamb chops were pretty good as well. Ambiance is great too and one of the nicer places post COVID.
100% halal food! The ambiance takes all the points here! Great setup, feels like a full Bollywood twilight zone.
Loved the food here, authentic deshi taste and their service. 10/10

Don't expect a Bangldeshi dining experience. It's just a hip "desi" Indian style restaurant. The food doesn't taste much better than any other Indian Buffet but the experience might be worth it! Great strawberry lassi though! Get it in a bottle specially in the pandemic very convenient!

We loved the food and it was our first time. Not only did they have great food, but great customer service. Shanzida was fantastic and super nice. She kept checking into make sure everything was great. Would definitely come back here!!!

was debating on whether or not to leave a review but I decided to save you guys the trouble since this place is hyped up on social media for god knows what. overpriced food , butter chicken was WAY TOO SWEET. crammed up tables and not enough space if you’re going with a big group. if you want good food please go somewhere else. would not recommend this place to anyone honestly. they don’t even give you a water jug I mean cmon who doesn’t give water jugs in restaurants man. anyways whatever i’m done.

100% halal food! The ambiance takes all the points here! Great setup, feels like a full Bollywood twilight zone. The food I have to say was just about average. The kati chicken roll, gol guppa/pani puri, & gulab jamin were mediocre. You can just about get it at any local Desi restaurant for half the price. Thumbs up to the waitress who recommended to come back and try the chicken tikka Mac and cheese - way after i ordered though. Shoutout to them using a Drake quote because it matters for the culture. Def recommend to check it out if you’re in the area.
The Bihari biriyani was trash. They added unnecessary herbs that with each bite I would taste the bitterness. Definitely not recommended!
Awesome Place to have some desi vibes and also able to enjoy desi food with desi test. Their Fuska and Masala tea are must.
Must visit

You can tell the owner put in a lot of work and effort on the smallest details of this restaurant. The decor and ambiance is great. The music here always gets you ready to start dancing. The food is so good!! If you like indian food, and indian music, definitely worth checking out
Ok
Awesome food, beautiful place.. Highly Recommended..
The food was okay and the services was really good and the employees were really friend but in the foods we found a hair and this happened 2 times but without that it was okay.

I went there tonight, and had a really good time. We got to take pictures on the Riksha displayed right when you enter, and the entire place had beautiful scenery on the walls and ceiling. The service was amazing. They take your temperature once you’re seated, and provide wipes for you to clean your hands. The menus are touchless scannable menus, and there’s a variety of items to choose from. The fuchka was delicious and a bit spicy for those who can’t handle spice. Everything else was good, some food could’ve used a bit more flavor or salt but overall delicious.

Holy schnikeys, the Butter Chicken was incredible! My wife loved the Shrimp Malai Curry. The Vegetable Biryani was wonderfully spicy, but wasn't as scrumtrulescent as the other dishes, but the chicken/lamb/shrimp biryani might be more flavorful. Excited to try more dishes. The Masala Chicken Sandwich looks amazing, can't wait to order next time.
I love the creativity, food was decent; didn’t like the Mac n cheese as much. Curry in small portions and too much white rice in ratio to the curry’s ordered. But overall the food: 3.4/5
Great authentic Indian food. Loved the ambience AND the food. Would HIGHLY highly recommend!!!

Honestly this place is cute and uses the gimmicks to attract customers. Food was a hit or miss. Pav baji was nasty while the mac n cheese was delicious. The desserts were over-priced and they charge you a 18% service fee. Overall a one time visit for the ig that’s all.
Just waste of time workers are not responsible as much suppose to be
Delicious bereyani and fuchka.  Didnt tried other stuff but the food is good and the service

Lovely atmosphere!  Definitely liked this location. The food was amazing, I never really tried indian food and I can say the food was amazing. From my entree to the dessert everything was great. Only issue was when I was waiting for my friend I was seated at the table with six chairs, the place was pretty empty at the time with two others seated on the other side of restaurant. While waiting the, waitress seats two at the table I am at which is weird because there was just one seat in between and not enough distance for social distancing. The restaurant was not even packed with many other seats all around. We moved once my friend arrived. Other than that, food was awesome.

I had high expectations for this place with all the positive reviews. Came here on a Sunday night. We got seated quickly, had reservations but there were plenty of seats available. We ordered the calamari chaat, guac dahi puri, chicken tikka mac and cheese and bihari kabab. I was pretty disappointed by the food. I enjoyed the calamari chaat the most. Chicken tikka mac and cheese was too cheesy. Guac dahi puri was okay, but I’ve had better dahi puri without guac. The bihari kabab I barely tried as I was full and took it to go. The portions are small but the prices are cheap so it makes sense. The decor is nice, and the service is great, hence the three stars. Not my cup of chai unfortunately.
The BEST gol gappe in NYC. The music & ambience is a great escape from the fast life, feels like you’ve travelled back in time. Loved it!
Very authentic food . The fuska filling was so cold and delicious 🤣🤣 And the Pav bhaji .. well I ate the veggies but  only those green salad. 🤣
Good food at a decent price.
Below average food and service. They don’t have Half of the items from their menu. Doesn’t recommend and would not return.
Brings back lots of memories

Worst place ever ....meat dishes filled up with veggies,(menu does says pepper)   . But who put big chunks of green pepper,  corn , carrots in lamb dishes 🤔.  On asking raita with biryani server says will have to see if it's available. And shows up with 3 tbsp of raita. Restaurant serving biryani and meat  dishes don't have sufficient raita ???? And yes they won't serve you plain Naan as they don't have it .... if u r not buttery or garlic person be prepared to get unhealthy.  I think regular Naan doesn't requires any extra ingredients . 🤔 Just had to left uneaten my 4 dishes. Thanks for making our evening dinner worst ever .
Excellent food. Love the butter chicken and Mac n cheese with a spicy kick.
The meat in lamb bihari was not fully cooked. The customer service is very poor. I had to wait for more than 20 min just to get a cup of yogurt. The quantity of rice with the dishes was very less.
Awesome food great service. Handled Covid-19 CDC protocols wonderfully... thank u
Nice environment, nice and friendly staff, the food was good, i just didn’t like the chicken karai but other then that everything else was good 👍🏽👍🏽👍🏽👍🏽
I had ordered Masala Chicken Samwich, which was pretty decent. But was bit surprised at the chips that came with because it was kurkure. They can be bought from any South Asian supermarket.
went there first time . It’s amazing I loved it . Cheap and good best restaurant love it . #kN I love the food Amazing. Best service ever (#shanzida)
The steak was amazing and my personal favorite is mac and cheese with chicken Tikka is beyond good :)

The place has nice outdoor dining! Even though our food order came late, the staff was extremely nice and caring. It was a busy night, so we weren't upset. They brought out my sisters birthday cake and even played Diljit Singh's "Happy Birthday" song without even requesting!! They offered us tea on the house (due to the late serving), and even let us take pictures inside the restaurant (with masks on, of course). Staff is super nice!! Would definitely come again!

Restaurant looks nice, it has a nice vibe to it. Service is good. Food is good. I ordered chicken tikka mac and cheese because a lot of people recommended. Personally, I did like it a lot, it was very good :) We also had pav bhajie, fusca and calamari chaat. I didn't like the fusca. I really enjoyed the pav bhajie, really tasty masala. I liked the calamari Chaat somewhat, it was interesting. There's lots of Bollywood posters on the ceiling and paintings of Bollywood actors in the wall. If you have seen 90's Bollywood(Indian) movies, you will enjoy the nostalgia. They play very nice old school Hindi(Indian) music too. I rate the place 8/10.

I tried their few dishes was alright but specifically the butter chicken was expected to be good but that also disappointed me. Secondly I order butter nearly 10$ and they used cheapest burger bun regular.

A whole lot of masti in this gem in Steinway!! The lamb Karahi was amazing I also got the Jhal Muri which was spicy and made me feel like I was back home in Dhaka eating on the streets! They have baby taxi which was imported from Dhaka  that's just very different, I haven't sat on one for over 10 years so definitely felt special sitting on that! The artwork and music is also on point! I would highly recommend this place to my friends and family!!
Great authentic indian food with great service. All staffs were friendly. I will go back there again.

Amazing food! The ambience and vibes are great at Gully. Their chicken and lamb chops are soo good! I personally hate lamb chops but theirs were really really good, so flavorful. Staff was really nice and made sure I was always in good hands and was very attentive. They were very clean and made sure all tables and chairs were spotless prior to sitting! Definitely one of my favorite Indian spots in the city. Highly recommend!!

Best Desi spot in NYC!! Straight Gully vibes from back home!  I found this place on TIK TOK and I fell in love!! The food is amazing.. Sahi korma was the best I ever had! Masala Chicken Samwich was just perfect, for appetizers I got Fuska, and Mac & Chesse which was really good! The music is straight vibes!! Everyone must check this place out!!

Best food spot on Steinway hands down! Love all the fusion dishes and the fun decor. The ambiance is super friendly and great for a snack with friends. Jasia was super friendly and very informative about every dish, ask for her! The  food is also very fairly priced so you are able to try a bunch of dishes without hurting your wallet. Deffinitely try the chicken tikka mac and cheese and calamari chaat when you go!!

Amazing Gully Vibes! Made me feel like I was back home in a gully somewhere ! The tunes are amazing. The food is very authentic and their fusion dishes are amazing. I loved Fuska, Calamari Chaat and the Desi Wales Bao! I recommend everyone to try !!
I went here for the first time Wednesday, the food was great. The chicken tinka Mac and cheese is to die for. Alfonse was very helpful in deciding what kind of tea to drink
Amazing food, amazing vibes! Must try the Mac and Cheese, calamari chaat! And the Kashmiri cold brew to go is bombb!!
This place is my go to for my desi cravings. Also I love the decor and outdoor seating area!

I HIGHLY recommend that you don’t order food from here. The food quality is terrible. The previous reviews all stated this, and I can confirm that this restaurant is a waste of money. Please look else where for quality Indian food, this place is complete trash.

Seeing the crowd and decorations, I expected the food would be great as well, but it wasn’t. Nothing I ate felt was made original, fuska was not filled up, and even the lamb burger that I ordered had a weird taste, that also with kurkure( store brought chips) on the side, like really disappointed.. 👎

I went there with very high expectation about to get good indian food . First thing during the covid crises they didn't had mask on their faces. Second the restaurant was also not so clean. I ordered chicken tikka mac and cheese and that was the most unhealthiest meal i ever had.. it was just cheese nothing else and cheese was in alot of quantity and then i ordered butter chicken and garlic naan.. the food was below average. After some time that food made me sick 🤢  I will never recommend this restaurant . 👎
The servicing is not good, the servers show a lot of attitude. They take long to bring food. They don't care about customers.
The waiters know how to welcome guests. The food was so good everything was perfect except the rice order naan instead.

Pretty good place to eat the naan was really good and the dishes were really nice my favorite was the butter chicken. The rice however is so-so and it’s like $5 for the rice which has too much cardamom. The food was fireeeeee other than that

My wife and I love Indian food. We got a flyer in the mail for this place and decided it was worth checking out.  We made the decision to go on a Friday night in the summer. Since we got there at an early time for dinner (6:30 pm), it was easy to get seated. Notably, they have a 45 min seating policy once food arrives.  Our server came out and asked if we were cool with either soda or water. We decided water and they brought out Poland spring bottles. Notably, the place does not serve alcohol.  We placed or orders and the food came out in about 15 mins. The Chicken Tikka Mac and Cheese was hands down our fave part of the night. We also both really liked our entrees. I love the creamy consistency of the sauces for both the Saag and Korma. Other Indian places have sauces that are pretty runny.  The vibes were chill, the Indian music playing at the place gave it a nice ambiance, and the food was really delicious.  Highly recommend you check this place out when you’re in Astoria.

Came to this place because it was suggested by instagram But the food was not authentic for sure not like real Indian cuisine they weren’t kidding when they said “urban desi food”. And don’t get me started with them not having certain things on the menu such as masala chai, water & Indian soda. You come to a restaurant expecting to get what you want but every time you ask the waitress they have bad news and say they don’t have this/that available. I had very high expectation coming here super excited but I left knowing I wouldn’t come to this place again. Cool for pictures and presentation but service is trash and food is mediocre. Wouldn’t really recommend.
Good is horrible
The food was decent quality, but it's not worth the hype. I had the butter chicken from there, which was very sweet. Also, the manager/owner came off rude.
I'm always looking for a place that makes Indian street food and this place is great! Try the fuska, calamari chaat (not traditional but so good) and chicken biryani.

I had the Vindaloo Chicken.  Pros: The food was good. It was the right kind of spice for me; not too spicy.  - Waitress was friendly.  Cons: - Unable to have a proper conversation due to loud music. It feels like being in a club instead of a restaurant.  - Mostly sauce & potatoes; not enough chicken.  - Manager/owner came of rude/mean.
Food was great, We recently ordered takeout!
The food is amazing.  This is during the social distancing thing so,  I can't speak to the service. But! The food is amazing!

Staff was friendly. I can see why it’s an Instagram hype because of the set up of the place but the food was nothing spectacular. The chicken tikka Mac n cheese was just a blob of so much cheese and hardly any macaroni or chicken, it was unbearable. The butter chicken was SO SO sweet, I didn’t even need dessert. The garlic naan was good though. They gave us chai on the house too so that was a nice gesture.

I had made a reservation here for two and when I arrived five minutes prior to the time the host let me know it would be a little wait. No biggie. My issue is that a friend of the hosts' came in after us and was seated prior to us being seated-even though we arrived before them and had made a reservation. The food was mediocre at best, I tried fuchka and jhal muri and both lacked flavor. I ordered biryani as a main dish and it was really oily. The service was absolutely terrible. Once we were done and paid the host came around to check in and I mentioned I was waiting for a to go container and he said he'd check on that. He didn't check on it (surprise surprise) and was chatting away to other friends/diners. I waited another five minutes for it until eventually I was fed up and left. I wanted to try it because of all the hype around it and its cool walls of art but I for sure will not be going back.
(Translated by Google) Pav Bhaji & Tea 2  (Original) Pav Bhaji & Tea 🤩
Good food. Good music.
I had best birthday ever!!! Thanks Shanzida for the amazing hospitality and authentic food. It’s hard to find place like this. True value of your money and quality time guaranteed.
Celebrated my friend’s birthday at The Gully, loved the vibe and food was great!  People who work there are super nice!!
Highly recommend. However don't ask for extra spicy curry,  you might end up burning your taste buds. Very delicious food otherwise...
This spot is worth a visit. They have large portions for reasonable prices. Constantly neat and with good ambience. Will come visit again.
Excellent food and service!
Vanessa was amazing waitress! Super accommodating. The food was delish. The Mac and cheese is to die for.
only for decorations food and services are so bad .
Not my cup of tea,  the presentation is good and the atmosphere is nice, but the main issues arise with the food prices and how good it is. I would say that the food wasn't the best for the price.
The food is amazing and the customer service is great also. It's a great place to have a Pakistani/Indian feel if you're craving some amazing desi food. The decor inside is a work of art
Best indian food i tasted so far. Highly recommend this place for anyone who likes indian food and for those who want to try it.

Visited the Gully in December 2019, the food was amazing. I was really impressed by the decor inside the restaurant. However the Masala Tea was my favourite. Only thing I would recommend is increasing the portion sizes!
Nicely decorated casual eatery with Bollywood posters. Food was good. We had chicken kati roll, bihari kabab and calamari chaat.
I was amazed. The food was so good, the atmosphere was so nice, and the service was exceptional. I would definitely recommend and would love to visit again.
Nice restaurant but the food is not that good compared to other Indian restaurants in Queens. It is decent.
Very yummy food, that came out quickly and didn't cost very much!

So my friend & I recent went to this place have to say, over priced and over rated food! Lol not to mention the owner deleted half of the negative reviews I saw before going to this place the negative comments no longer exist!
Best indoor street food!!
Great food and music

Gives total desi vibes, really loved the songs they were playing... food was great as well, we ordered masala chicken samwich, chicken tikka platter, fuchka and mango lassi....I wished they had given less spinach or green... not because I don’t like them but it’s just unnecessary on the plate in my opinion. Overall a nice place to hangout with ur family and friends.
Order less food, don’t get a lot. It will full you up real quick. The food is good. But I felt like we were on top of other guest in the restaurant and very little space between the tables.

Basically, the quality of the food didn't match the hype. They didn't have their most well-known dish, the chicken tikka mac and cheese during their opening hours. The bun of Lamb burger was hard as a rock. As if the buns were just taken out from the fridge and warmed lightly. The only thing I enjoyed there was the decor and mango lassi. And our waitress was very nice and friendly.
The food, ambience & service was incredible. Shanzida made our experience even better! Highly recommend this place. Amazing butter chicken & chai

It was nice atmosphere. Our waitress was great and very friendly.  Food was great.  Reason for the three stars, we had made a reservation to celebrate valentine's day 3 weeks before but their system couldn't find it.  We waited for seat and they sat us on a shared table.  That was okay, they were busy I understand that.  But I told the manager about this bad experience he started arguing back.  No accommodation, we just got it's not their fault. It's the system.  And we as customer paid the price for their system. He never checked back if everything was ok.  Management needs training.
Very disappointed .no flavor at all.
Loved the food and the ambiance. Tried to fuchka, cha, chicken tikka biriyani and strawberry lassi. All very tasty. Will go back soon.

I came with many high hopes and was, unfortunately, disappointed. The guac dahi puri was literally only guacamole and yogurt, plus some sev and parsley for garnishing. The flavor was completely bland. Adding a sauce, masala, or additional filling would definitely up the flavor. I didn't order the fuska but I believe people are confusing the two as pictures of the fuska have a sauce and different filling. The guac dahi puri is NOT the same as the fuska.The chicken tikka biryani was very salty, and had a tad bit too much masala. The only thing I enjoyed was the chicken tikka mac and cheese. I hope that the flavor profiles improve because the idea of such a place is cool (the inside is cozy but pretty!). The prices are also reasonable, at least in my opinion.

I came for the first time and tried their Chicken Tikka biryani and Aloo Unda. The biryani tasted very off. The chicken tikka itself was decent and some were burnt. The rice as well was flavorless. The second dish which was aloo unda was kind of flavorless as well. I understand that there was supposed to be potato in it, but i tasted more egg than a mixture. The sauces were alright. The white sauce that came with the biriyani did not make it taste any better.
Food was actually very average. Mac and cheese was the highlight. Fuschka was completely off. Mains were all ok. Quite dissapointing.
The food was average. As a Indian, I expected more.

Social media exaggerated how good the food would be, the chicken tikka mac n cheese DOESN’T even have chicken in it!! It was over priced I ordered desert it was LITERALLY one piece of Rasmali for $5 thats such a rip off and I understand its a restaurant but that’s completely making customers a fool. And it it uncomfortable when the staff are looking right at you. This place is a beautiful place nice art work and colors only lack is that their food could have been 100 times better.
Food is ok , not worth the price.

Their food was great like really good. I do reccomend it for the food how ever I give it only 3 stars because when I told them I was here and I needed a table for 3 people I was just standing there waiting for a table for a long time. Especially there were open tables and I was just left there. And someone else had to get to me. Then when I was finally seated no one asked me if I wanted anything as I was waiting for the rest of my party. Not even a menu. But the food is good and the decor is great.

My party and I were coming in with really high expectations and were excited to try this restaurant given all the glowing reviews. However, the night started off on the wrong foot the minute we stepped in. We had a 7:30PM reservation and despite our entire party being present, the host gave our table away to another walk-in party because he did not accurately verify if the walk-in party had a reservation. They tried to accommodate or save themselves by offering us a table to share with another party, but neither party wanted share a table as everyone wants to eat in their own space. We had to wait another 30 minutes just to be able to sit down. Once seated, the waiter was very nice, accommodating and really knew the menu and what recommendations to make. For appetizers, we ordered the fuska, the chicken tikka Mac n' cheese, chicken burger and lamb chops. The fuska was a standard version of pain puri, which one can get at any Indian establishment. The chicken tikka Mac n' cheese and chicken burger were the only highlights of the evening. The lamb chops were overly salty and not a good balance of flavors. For entrees we ordered the chicken biryani and butter chicken, which was also standard for any Indian restaurant. All in all, it was a standard overly-hyped restaurant with poor customer service and a basic menu.
Overrated....very disappointing.....foods comes in very small portions...
I ordered lamb biryani and lamb chop. But, biryani had no flavor, no butter. And They didn't serve lamb chop, they served lamb tandoori it has too food color
Food quality is good .. But Their customer service isn't good tho.. Their was so many people and just 2 server.. and the most bad part was we had to do our own to go pack🙄🙄
Went to this place after being recommended to check it out. I just had 4 plates of Fuchkas. Definitely going again. The store had a nice desi vibe. Loved it! Highly recommended!
Ordered Pav Bhaji and chicken tikka roll. Kinda oily, not up to hype and the roll Roti was oily seems like it was all made in one single pan. One time visit for me.

This place is truly a gem. Full of art work and dope food. Definitely a must try spot in QUEENS. Name another place that has Chicken Tikka MAC&CHEESE . It’s the only spot I know that offers this . Mind you they have one crazy menu from the Kati Rolls to the Masala Chai . Everything honestly tastes great. Also it’s worth the money and not expensive at all .  Ambiance- 10/10 Service - 10/10 Shoutout to Vanessa WiFi - Not Sure Parking - Good Luck
Very good place to get Indian food

Best place to eat with family.I really enjoyed the chicken ticka biriyani.My mom says that the best part was the mango lassi.I personally recommend this restaurant for lunch/dinner with family and friends.Also,there was great service and came to ask us if everything was okay,which we really liked. Shanzida was a big help.

So this was the first time actually in the place! We ordered to go before and because the food was too good we had to go and try more food! We tried Aloo tikki and calamari as our appetizers and lamb biriyani was our main course. This amazing meal was ended with falooda and Rasmalia tres leches! It has the cool vibe and service is also good. Can't wait for next time !
Modern looking place but very over priced. Taste is okay

Honestly the food was phenomenal. I ordered the lamb Karahi and it was so so delicious!! My cousin ordered the lamb burger and she gave it two thumbs up, my aunt ordered the chicken biryani and it was tasty but a bit too spicy. Lastly my boyfriend ordered the chicken chops which he really loved!! The mango lasi is super yummy also. Customer service was great. The ambiance is so special, the art and aesthetic is awesome.  We tried the mac and cheese because it is so raved about, but it's the one item we could have ALL done without, it's basically a cheese fondue, I wasn't a fan.  The only thing that could use some improving is the bathroom (there is only one) and it could just be cleaner and more stocked. My rating is for the food though.  I would definitely recommend.
Fantastic!  Great food quality and very busy! Took us 30 min to get a table because we were 7 people but the food quality and service was totally worth!!

Amazing mix of food. Came all the way from Philly to see what this was about and have to say, I am not disappointed. The Mac&Cheese could have used a bit more noodles, whole thing was drenched in cheese. Everything else was delicious!
The food doesn't taste good and is not worthy in that price. I'll rather eat from the halal cart than going there. Only good thing is restaurant look which is quite attractive and creative.
BEST FOOD EVER! Coming from a punjabi, that only chases spices in dishes.. every dish I had surpassed my expectations! Cant wait to come next time.
Great food and unique style
we had our new years eve dinner at Gully. We had a great experience on their busy night. Food was great and service  was unbeatable. We received excellent attention from Vanessa.
I'd wish this place would have lived to the hype. It's definitely nice inside and picture worthy and the Mango Lassi was good. But everything else required salt and some more flavor
Awesome place, waitress were solovely and friendly .. thanks for your good service,  keep it up

Honestly exceeded my expectations. Food was on point. Staff was friendly and the vibe/atmosphere was super chill. It's the traditional Indian food with a twist. Definitely would come back to try more things!
Amazing experience, great service, super friendly staff and the food is really top level. If you haven’t been here you’re playing games. Period.
It was the best place I ever when.  omg the food is soo good  it an Indian food 🤤🤤🤤😍😍😍
Ambience was excellent but food taste wise was ok nothing surprising, very basic..

Their decoration wad very good, music was also good . food is so far good but one thing I noticed they need to more active on their customer service. Price is little expensive than other place. Small amount of food .

Finally I went there 😂 if you are not worry about your money and you can pay little extra for food ! that’s the place for you highly recommended ! The food is way too good ! I thought it’s gonna be a huge place but it’s just small eatery place with traditional decoration ! Fuchka, Pabh-Bhaji, Shrimp malai curry and lamb chops are highly recommended ! Food taste good but it’s short amount of food if you compare with the money ! But all over, Service was good !
Definitely a unique vibe to this place, good food, and decent prices.
Fuska needs to improve. Over priced and overrated. Good flavors though but I felt rushed to finish. *Bro stop taking my plates away!!*
Awesome...genuine 90 Bollywood vibes!!
Good spot.  Appetizers needs to be sent before mains.  But the food is good in general.  Tikka Mac and Cheese was great a go to.
Food was great. Service was ok. Got no water refills. Staff appeared to be busy tho. We also got served 1 app with 1 entree, and the other app and entree came later... strange. Food was amazing tho

The food was amazing! I loved the atmosphere and the music. They had a blend of everything you can imagine. Highly recommend this place. The staff was friendly and we even ended up getting complimentary cha at the end of our meal!
Food out here is amazing!! Not just the food, also the service is great! Will certainly come back !
Great Food and environment! Staff is wonderful as well! Reminds you of Bollywood movies with the Bollywood original music! Must visit spot!

If you all get amazed by the Bollywood ambience, quotes and posters and think you will get to eat desi food from Mumbai. No! You don't! The place is run by Bangali people and they don't even know the proper names of dishes. It just does not taste आमची मुंबई

I have been to the gully twice now. My friends took me there the first time and omg I absolutely fell in love with the food! So far I had fuska, chicken tikka Mac and cheese,  chicken biryani, pav bhaji, their chai and mango lassi. Their food did not disappoint me at all. Food was amazing. Their space is small but I love the creativity they put into their walls. The second time I went there, I took my family with me. Even they loved their food. The gully is definitely a great place to try some amazing Indian food. Good customer service as well. I just wish they expand this place in the future Bcz it does get pretty busy and they don’t have much seating arrangement. I’ll definitely be back when I crave some Indian food . 👌🏼
Great service and great food..hats off to shanzida

A mediocre Indian place. The overall vibe was good but music quality was poor. Food portions were hilariously small and pricess were unreasonable compared to quantity. The spicy street food and kati rolls were good but the burgers and lamb were very dry and uncooked. This place needs a lot of improvement.

We made reservations for 8pm and a lady called around to make sure that all 13 people will be there on time but when we went there at 8:01pm there was no reserved table ready for us. The person in charged told us to wait for 30 minutes. Basically it was pointless to make reservations a day before for a huge crowd when we all had to wait additional half an hour. We all were standing as the restaurant was packed. Lesson learned not to call to make any reservations in this place. I was there with my toodler who already lost his patience that's why I had to walk outside in the pouring rain with him just so that he is okay then we all can eat dinner later on peacefully. My first impression with this place was extremely terrible due to unprofessional wait time for the large party eho made reservations but thanks to the yummiest food I forgot about the horrible wait. It's a gem of a place in Steinway with fusion of Bangali and Indian... I loved everything that we ordered. I will recommend all the foodie just to stop by once. The person in charge gave a slice of a cake in the end while we were waiting for our take home food.
Yassss
Closes at unreported times. After a long journey from flushing, we were left unable to eat. Very sad.
Food was good and service was fast . I like that place

Came here on a weekend afternoon. Was not too crowded. Food was pretty good. The katti rolls were excellent. The chicken tikka mac and cheese was too cheesy for my taste buds. Wish it was crispy on top. But loved the chicken tikka spin on it. Can't wait to try some of their other items, like their burgers. Our waitress, Vanessa was attentive and provided great service. Definitely coming back here again. Loved that they were playing classic Bollywood songs from the 90s..brought me back to simpler times.

Came here for a birthday dinner and it was amazing! The service(shout out to Rafi for being a great host), the food, and the ambiance of the place all together made for a great night. Would definitely recommend!

Loved their food so much. Mango lassi was so delicious and the chicken karahi too! And their pani puri is the best I’ve ever had. Definitely going back to try to the chicken tikka mac&cheese. Recommended 💯

I came back for the second time and was really impressed by the food and particularly the service. Vanessa was absolutely phenomenal in all aspects. She ensured that my food not only arrived in a timely fashion, but went above and beyond to make sure I was pleased. At the conclusion of my meal, she came out with an UNEXPECTED complimentary chai and biscuits. I highly recommend this spot to anyone!
Great ambiance not the greatest food. Had the chicken kadahi biryani and chicken Tikka Mac and cheese. The Mac and cheese was 5 stars as was the environment.
Great food and atmosphere.
Food Was great nice place

The Gully is a beautiful restaurant with amazing food and gorgeous aesthetics. Visitors experience the flavors of the East as the restaurant serves South Asian street food. Hands down, the best item in the menu is the Chicken Tikka Mac and Cheese which combines a traditional western dish with a Desi twist. The service is amazing, the waitress always finds yo at the right time and is ready to serve. The walls are painted in graffiti that shows the culture of South Asia. This is my third visit and I will continue to eat here in the near future.
Food was extremely delicious, great food ever halal
Amazing. Everything was hands down delicious. Ho to munch spot from now on!!!

This is my go to spot whenever I’m in Astoria. The Mac and cheese and Kati rolls are bomb. Just recently ordered through Uber eats and the food still tasted fresh. Great vibes, great service and great food. Highly recommend.

Food was extremely delicious. Service was really fast and the staff was extremely kind and showed great hospitality. Just the portion size is a little small but still was really good. The Chicken Tikka Mac and Cheese is a must try their most popular item.

I had my sisters bday gathering here and we had almost every item on the menu, the food was great, location was perfect and staff were very nice. I can only give this place what it deserves all 5 stars!!

The food is amazing here everytime. I go here very often, never had a bad experience. The staff is very nice and the environment is amazing. The food is also very delicious. Especially the goat biryani and the chicken tikka Mac and cheese.
Their decoration is awesome but need to improve on providing better service and need to hire better chef to provide better foods!

Love this place. I order  Mac and cheese tikka with  a desi taste very good biriyani pot was testy. Everything was good and  the setting. U definitely get the feeling of gully with old songs, and The masala Cha

Was so amazed to find out that the place is owned by the same person who owns two of my other favorite restaurants Nur thai and Lulus chinese. No wonder I was so happy with the food and service. We ordered almost everything on the menu and it tasted great. The service was good and fast as well. Would definitely recommend if you are craving some good indian food!
So far so good. Will come back soon again to try rest of the food on the menu.
Food is slamming!!! Everyone that works there is Awsome and amazing service!!! Thanzir helped me pick out what I wanted to eat 👏🏼

If you’re looking for South Asian cuisine, this place won’t disappoint. The service was also fantastic, our waitress was very friendly. I would recommend this place.
The food was delicious and great service ,nicely decorated and very desi style which I loved it. Stuff were very nice and music is too cool.👌
The food was amazing. I had their fuchka and loved it! But the service was not good at all which took off 2 stars.
Food was really good. Service was little slow, but taste of the food worth the waitting.
Had to wait little more than 30 minutes  for food. But the staff at the restaurant were really nice. They gave us free chai and fuchka for the long wait. Food was really good. 10 out of 10.

The food here is great !!!!! I came here on numerous occasions and I can honestly say the food taste better and better everytime I go. I just had dinner with my entire family here tonight and everyone loved it. The food the atmosphere and staff deserves a 5 STAR. Thanks again for great experience

Me and my colleague were on a business trip to NY and on our last night randomly walked into this place, we made a to-go order, and boy oh boy, the food was so amazing! I forgot the name of the place, as I was so determined to leave a positive review, I did my research until I found the name and the address. Thanks again Gully guys! hopefully will be back again someday!

Decor is unique. And chicken tikka mac and cheese was tasty. But the portions for everything were so small. And to make matters worse, most of each order was onions and peppers. Very little meat served. Disappointed by the value here.
Great experience.

The place was great. Loved the service. The food was amazing especially the chicken tikka mac and cheese something way worth trying .  Something sounded weird in a way but delicious. I love this place and want to go many more times.
Worst customer service and food wasnt good at all. Just full of spices. If social media is your thing then worth the visit for pic purpose. Will not come back or recommend.

We had the Kati rolls (paneer for our little girl - which she loved, lamb and chicken) and they were all excellent. the lamb was the star if you’re looking to only pick one.  The Tikka Mac & Cheese is a standout, and worth traveling from anywhere in the city to try.  We also had Chicken Kadari with garlic naan, which was also great.  This place is a gem.  Not sure why it’s only ranked 4 out of 5.

Ok! This is a nice place to visit if you like the ambient and the fancy setting. The decor is very nice. Unique art work. If you like that type of thing then  this is a good place. Now let’s talk about the food. If you are looking for authentic Indian or Bangladeshi food this is not the place. Their “fuska” was not that good. Bit bland. They have some nice ideas like the chicken tikka masala Mac and cheese which feels like they took tikka masala and mixed it with krafts Mac and cheese. All the curry was over powering with heave cream/butter. I did like the biryani. I found the portion bit small compared to other Desi spots. Almost all the dish had nice heat(spicy) to it. I defiantly liked that. Overall this place is not bad. It’s a good concept of mixing American food with Indian food. It’s the new trend. The service was very good. I would go back to this place if I’m in the area and crave Indian food.

Their customer service and decor was great, it’s their food that was not good at all. I requested to have my Fuska and the chicken tikka Kati roll spicy - and in return they poured raw red pepper on it. My friend that I went with choked immensely because of all the raw red pepper. I then choked on the same raw red pepper that was on the chicken tikka Kati roll. The chicken tikka mac n’cheese was not good either. I actually got sick after having a quarter bowl of that. It tasted like butter chicken and Mac N’ cheese mixed. In a nutshell it’s not my kind of food honestly, I’m big on food. I think the best thing here was their customer service and the interior decoration. The hand dryer in the bathroom is also no good.

I've been to The Gully about five times now and each time I go I have zero regrets. The food and service are amazing and the atmosphere is just as good. Shoutout to the chefs and employees for the overall great experience.

Interesting menu and I liked most of the items we ordered - Chicken Tikka Mac n Cheese, Chicken Kadari, Shrimp Malaikari, Lamb Burger, Bihari Kati Roll. A big downside for me though was the loud music even during the day - I could barely hear my dining companions and we had to shout at each other. I'd hesitate to return only because of that.
This place is amazing.  Staff is very attentive, the food is great and easy on the wallet for sure.  Will definitely go back
Tried this place already with a friend and I am obsessed since then. I liked the good mood and tasty food and drinks. I recommend this place.
Absolutely great place to eat. I took my Girl Scouts there and they were in awe with the service and the food. She was so happy with the beauty of the. Highly recommend this restaurant.

Best place you’ll ever go to.

Great design interior and artwork. Seating isn’t the most comfortable and everyone is pretty close in proximity to other people. Food was good, flavorful and delicious. Mango lassi is average Bihari kebab was average Chicken tikka mac and cheese was delicious and u should try it Shrimp malai was delicious and u should try it Just right portion sizes Average service, received an incorrect order but was corrected. Awesome food and vibes. No alcohol but you really don't need it with how good the food is. The chicken tikka mac and cheese and the pav bhaji were my favorites!

Every dish is worth trying! Great food with awesome costumer service. Menu is perfect, something for everyone's taste. Very comforting and scenic atmosphere! Will be going back for sure!
Amazing service, great food, great music and overall a welcoming atmosphere.

Gully has been the ultimate street food experience literally in the heart of Queens. There is beautiful street art reminiscent of words, movies and celebrities I grew up seeing on tv. Besides the experience, the food is exceptional. The Dahi Puri, Chicken tikka mac n cheese, lamb burger and chicken tikka Kati roll are literally my favorite dishes. I love everything on the menu and have no complaints. The chai and mango lassi are great drinks for anyone that wants authentic Indian flavors. The service is always on par and everyone is very attentive. Overall, Gully has taken the average home cooked food and elevated it to a dynamite eating experience that's filled with culture and memories. I highly recommend everyone try it out. Thank you to the owners for recognizing the importance of our culture and doing something so innovative for the community.

This place has to offer the worst service ever. I ordered Calamari chat as a starter, then mac n cheese and lamb beriyani. We only received the mac n cheese after 30 mins i asked our server. Where is our lamb beriyani!!? She said ‘’I will check in the back’’ she never came back to our table. I called the manager he responded how sorry they are and how our food was mistakenly delivered to a wrong table. He also offered us a free dessert, which  we never received, after waiting a while we just left, but most shocking thing was they weren’t even busy and server never came to us to apologize or checked up on us she just took my card to ran it and didn’t even say anything. We are Very disappointed and we will not ever visit again.

Environment: Good instagram-worthy backdrop. Seating is too tight.  Food: Calamari was the only good dish, which was an appetizer. Mac and cheese was ok. Chicken and Lamb kadari was disappointing. Fuchka was way below average. Chai was the most washed out chai I ever had.  Over-all, the food is hyped up. I recommend the place only for the backdrop.
Best Indian food I’ve had in Astoria.

First thing’s first, if you could, I’d recommend booking a table. I tried booking a table online but there were issues with it. If it works, I’d stick with it. Waiting can be an issue.  We were greeting by Razeeb, the owner, and he was very polite and accommodating to the long wait we had. He offered us chai, water, or any sort of drink we would like while we waited. Once we were seated, we gave our order and food was great! We were served food in tin cups and tin plates just like back home. Flavor was amazing, I recommend getting the Aloo Tikki and Kadai Chicken. Tanzir recommended his favorites and indeed they were really good. Polite people, great workers, great vibes. Def check it out if you’re in town.  P.S.: Parking is a nightmare. I suggest using ride share services or train.

Staff is very welcoming and service is amazing. I really love the food here, chicken tikka Mac and cheese is a must. The restaurant is beautiful and inexpensive. Thank you guys for the amazing experience. Will definitely be returning.

Cool decor and vibe and prices are reasonable, but mediocre food at best. There are some interesting fusion options but we only tried the Chicken Tikka Mac n Cheese, which is just an over-hyped, overly sweet, otherwise flavorless and spiceless butter chicken with some cheese and a few macaroni noodles mixed in. Our Chicken Kadari had a decent flavor, but was also washed out with a sweet sauce. Plus we found a hair in our dish, which was replaced with a new one and we were given a discount on our bill...but not one person ever apologized to us. I understand that hairs in the food happens sometimes, but the staff seemed almost annoyed that we pointed it out and wanted a new dish.  Overall, Gully slots in somewhere between authentic and fusion cuisine, with some traditional staples and a few Instagram hype-worthy creations. Unfortunately, they do neither particularly well. At least the chai was pretty good.

This place just opened up about 3 weeks ago. The owner also owns Nur Thai in Queens blvd and Sugar and coal. Their food is top notch. It's not even that expensive. Their fuska is cheap and very good compared to most fushka trucks. Their Butter Chicken and Tikka Chicken is very good. The best part about "The Gully" is the atmosphere. The inside is astonishing with all the details they have of over 200 old Bollywood movie posters.
They get a 5 star for looks of the food and location, but negative stars for taste. Its straight disgusting food. If you like it only god knows youll eat pet food if it were hyped and rate it a 5
Great place! If you are a Bollywood lover, you’ll appreciate it!

Really fun and hip place to go to! We were so excited to try the chicken Tikka Mac n cheese and it was SO good!! If I had known the portion sizes were small I would have ordered more. The chicken Tikka Mac n cheese, fuska, biryani, butter chicken are all so good! However the sizes are small so if you intend to share, you should order more! Highly recommend this place! It was so fun and the food was so good! The owner is so kind!!! And my friends and I stayed for a good half an hour afterwards just to take pictures!

I tried this restaurant's food first time today, because of the hype on IG, i am so disappointed, the food was nasty,  and over pricey for a little small container, I ordered chicken tikka Mac and Cheese, it tasted  like tomato sauce, and chicken tikka did not even taste like chicken tikka, it was not well marinated like how the chicken tikka should be marinated, and in Butter chicken they used the canned tomato sauce as well. Iv been to many restaurants in my life, and i have never been this disappointed.  this restaurant is good for people who do not know what actual  desi food tastes like.  dont go by IG.     do your research. I am never going back and I would not recommend this to my friends or anyone.
Portions were small but food was delicious! Chicken tikka biryani / Fuska / Mac and cheese chicken / lamb burger really Good really recommended

New hip restaurant in Steinway. The food is to die for. A mix of Desi and America food. The decor is fantastic.
